member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE
member.summary: The WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE enumeration is a list of commonly used security identifiers (SIDs). Programs can pass these values to the function to create a SID from this list.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinNullSid
member.summary: Indicates a null SID.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinWorldSid
member.summary: Indicates a SID that matches everyone.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinLocalSid
member.summary: Indicates a local SID.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinCreatorOwnerSid
member.summary: Indicates a SID that matches the owner or creator of an object.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinCreatorGroupSid
member.summary: Indicates a SID that matches the creator group of an object.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinCreatorOwnerServerSid
member.summary: Indicates a creator owner server SID.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinCreatorGroupServerSid
member.summary: Indicates a creator group server SID.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinNtAuthoritySid
member.summary: Indicates a SID for the Windows NT authority account.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinDialupSid
member.summary: Indicates a SID for a dial-up account.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinNetworkSid
member.summary: Indicates a SID for a network account. This SID is added to the process of a token when it logs on across a network. The corresponding logon type is LOGON32_LOGON_NETWORK.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinBatchSid
member.summary: Indicates a SID for a batch process. This SID is added to the process of a token when it logs on as a batch job. The corresponding logon type is LOGON32_LOGON_BATCH.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinInteractiveSid
member.summary: Indicates a SID for an interactive account. This SID is added to the process of a token when it logs on interactively. The corresponding logon type is LOGON32_LOGON_INTERACTIVE.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinServiceSid
member.summary: Indicates a SID for a service. This SID is added to the process of a token when it logs on as a service. The corresponding logon type is LOGON32_LOGON_SERVICE.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinAnonymousSid
member.summary: Indicates a SID for the anonymous account.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinThisOrganizationSid
member.summary: Indicates a SID present when the user authenticated from within the forest or across a trust that does not have the selective authentication option enabled. If this SID is present, then WinOtherOrganizationSid cannot be present.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinOtherOrganizationSid
member.summary: Indicates a SID present when the user authenticated across a forest with the selective authentication option enabled. If this SID is present, then WinThisOrganizationSid cannot be present.

member.name: WELL_KNOWN_SID_TYPE.WinBuiltinIncomingForestTrustBuildersSid
member.summary: Indicates a SID that allows a user to create incoming forest trusts. It is added to the token of users who are a member of the Incoming Forest Trust Builders built-in group in the root domain of the forest.
